{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c428a451-75ad-4a73-a489-833fb82d74cb","content":"Here are the issues I found with your `template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing required field `identity`** — Every .NET template must have an `identity` field (a unique identifier for the template).\n\n2. **Invalid `datatype` value** — The symbol `myParam` uses `\"datatype\": \"invalid-type\"`, which is not a valid datatype. Valid values include: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, `string`.\n\n3. **Missing `sourceName`** — While not strictly required, `sourceName` is typically expected for templates that perform name substitution.\n\n4. **Potentially conflicting `shortName`** — `\"build\"` may conflict with common CLI commands/aliases.\n\n**Minimum fix** — add `identity` and correct the datatype:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"author\": \"Test\",\n  \"classifications\": [\"Test\"],\n  \"identity\": \"Test.Template\",\n  \"name\": \"Test Template\",\n  \"shortName\": \"build\",\n  \"symbols\": {\n    \"myParam\": {\n      \"type\": \"parameter\",\n      \"datatype\": \"string\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b8f958d5-4470-4ed8-a5c2-3749e0df9997","outputTokens":275,"requestId":"A7E2:3835CB:15EA738:187446D:6A051DB2"},"id":"5147749a-f162-4d0c-9f9e-438cb9815f40","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:27.131Z","parentId":"3ef950c0-3b61-4196-87e5-0c654c71075b"}
